title: Murder probe as body found at factory
text:
Share on Twitter 
POLICE are investigating after the body of a man was found at a factory in Sydney’s southwest. 
About 7.30am police were called to the complex on Pine Rd, Yennorra after the discovery of the body. 
A crime scene has been established and the homicide squad brought in to investigate. 
Detectives from State Crime Command’s Homicide Squad are also on scene and treating the death as suspicious. 
At this stage the body is unidentified. Something going on at Pine Rd, Yennora.. Cops and camera crew everywhere. Blocked off what looks to be a warehouse. #sydney #news
